 */
function getWeaponEffectiveArea(integer|real weapon, integer|real cell, integer|real from) => Array<integer>;
function getWeaponEffectiveArea(integer|real weapon, integer|real cell) => Array<integer>;

/**
 * @brief Returns weapon weapon effects.
 *
 * @category weapon
 * @cost 125 ops
 *
 * @param[in] weapon (optional) The id of the weapon whose effects will be returned.
 * @return effects An array containing the effects of the weapon weapon. Each effect is itself an array
 *     of the form [type, min, max, turns, targets, modifiers]. - type is one of the effect
 *     constants: @ref EFFECT DAMAGE|EFFECT_DAMAGE, @ref EFFECT_HEAL, @ref
 *     EFFECT_ABSOLUTE_SHIELD, @ref EFFECT_RELATIVE_SHIELD, @ref EFFECT_DEBUFF, @ref
 *     EFFECT_BUFF_STRENGTH, @ref EFFECT_BUFF_AGILITY, @ref EFFECT_BUFF_MP, @ref
 *     EFFECT_BUFF_TP etc. - min and max are the minimum and maximum value of the effect (as
 *     shown in the market). - turns is the duration of the effect in number of turns. -
 *     targets represents the players that will be hit by this effect in the area. It is a
 *     binary combination of the constants: - @ref EFFECT_TARGET_ALLIES: Affects allies -
 *     @ref EFFECT_TARGET_ENEMIES: Affects enemies - @ref EFFECT_TARGET_CASTER: Affects the
 *     caster - @ref EFFECT_TARGET_SUMMONS: Affects summons - @ref EFFECT_TARGET_NON_SUMMONS:
 *     Affects non-summoned entities - modifiers represents the modifiers of the effect. It
 *     is a binary combination of the constants: - @ref EFFECT_MODIFIER_STACKABLE: The effect
 *     is stackable. - @ref EFFECT_MODIFIER_MULTIPLIED_BY_TARGETS: The effect is multiplied
 *     by the number of targets hit in the area. - @ref EFFECT_MODIFIER_ON_CASTER: Always
 *     affects the caster.
 */
function getWeaponEffects(integer|real weapon) => Array<Array>;
function getWeaponEffects() => Array<Array>;

