/**
 * @brief Returns a cell where your entity can use the chip chip on the entity entity.
 *
 * The returned cell is not necessarily the closest. If no cell is possible, the function
 * returns -1.
 * Example for throwing a @ref Rock: `` var cell = getCellToUseChip(CHIP_ROCK, enemy)
 * moveTowardCell(cell) useChip(CHIP_ROCK, enemy) ``
 *
 * @category fight
 * @cost 38080 ops
 *
 * @param[in] chip The chip that the entity wants to be able to use.
 * @param[in] entity The target entity.
 * @param[in] ignoredCells (optional) Table of cells to ignore. By default an empty array.
 * @return cell The cell where the chip can be used.
 */
function getCellToUseChip(integer|real chip, integer|real entity, Array<integer> ignoredCells) => integer;
function getCellToUseChip(integer|real chip, integer|real entity) => integer;

/**
 * @brief Determines a cell where your entity can use the chip chip on the cell cell.
 *
 * The returned cell is not necessarily the closest. If no cell is possible, the function
 * returns -1.
 *
 * @category fight
 * @cost 38080 ops
 *
 * @param[in] chip The chip that the entity wants to be able to use.
 * @param[in] cell The target cell.
 * @param[in] ignoredCells (optional) Table of cells to ignore. By default an empty array.
 * @return cell The cell where the chip can be used.
 */
function getCellToUseChipOnCell(integer|real chip, integer|real cell, Array<integer> ignoredCells) => integer;
function getCellToUseChipOnCell(integer|real chip, integer|real cell) => integer;

